      • uiReadyCredential

        public static CredentialBuilder uiReadyCredential()
        Constructs a builder for an active, ui ready credential. The user will have an automatically generated user name of the form "userN" and will have password "gw".

        There is no CC specific CredentialBuilder so this method can't be put on CredentialBuilder, where it really belongs.

        Returns:
        the credential builder

      • uiReadyUser

        public static UserBuilder uiReadyUser()
        Builder for constructing a new, active, user. The user will have an auto generated username and contact. The password for the user will be "gw". If no explicit methods are called to alter roles, the user will be given the adjuster role. If explicit methods are called then the user will just have the roles specified by those methods and there will be no automatic adding of the adjuster role. The user's group will be the root group, by default, use withFirstGroup() to override this.
        Returns:
        a new builder

      • uiReadyUser

        public static UserBuilder uiReadyUser(Group group)
        Builder for constructing a new, active, user in a particular group. The user will have an auto generated username and contact. The password for the user will be "gw". If no explicit methods are called to alter roles, the user will be given the adjuster role. If explicit methods are called then the user will just have the roles specified by those methods and there will be no automatic adding of the adjuster role.
        Parameters:
        group - the user's group; if null the user will be added to the root group. The user can be added to multiple groups using further calls to UserBuilderBase.withGroup(ValueGenerator)
        Returns:
        a new builder
